# Get the reviews per city
reviews_p_city = data %>%
  group_by(Hotel_location) %>%
  summarise(quantity = n()) %>%
  select(Hotel_location, quantity) %>%
  arrange(desc(quantity))

# Positivity evaluation regarding the count of words
pos = data %>%
  group_by(Reviewer_Nationality) %>%
  summarize(sum_pos = sum(Review_Total_Positive_Word_Counts), sum_neg = sum(Review_Total_Negative_Word_Counts)) %>%
  select(Reviewer_Nationality, sum_pos, sum_neg) %>%
  mutate(proportion = round(sum_pos / (sum_pos + sum_neg),2)) %>%
  arrange(desc(proportion))

# Combine the above to ideas into positivity evaluation accordig to nationality
pos = data %>%
  group_by(Reviewer_Nationality) %>%
  summarize(sum_pos = sum(Review_Total_Positive_Word_Counts), sum_neg = sum(Review_Total_Negative_Word_Counts)) %>%
  inner_join(reviews_p_nation, by='Reviewer_Nationality') %>%
  mutate(proportion = round(sum_pos / (sum_pos + sum_neg),2)) %>%
  filter(quantity > 8000) %>%
  arrange(desc(proportion))

# Compute the reviews per hotel which should give insight about the saturation of a market (low means high market saturation, high means low market saturation)
reviews_p_hotel = inner_join(reviews_p_city, hotels_p_city, by = 'Hotel_location') %>%
  rename(vol = quantity.x, hotels = quantity.y) %>%
  select(Hotel_location, vol, hotels) %>%
  mutate(reviews_p_hotel = vol / hotels)

# This part was hard-coded taken over from a team members python data exploration and was used to build the graph in the rpesentation, the dplyr code prior would have been the best practice, but was later added.

city    <- c('Amsterdam', 'Barcelona', 'London','Milan', 'Paris', 'Vienna') 
vol <- c(57436, 60149, 262301,37207, 59706, 38939)
reviews_p_hotel <- c(536.79, 285.07, 657.4,229.67, 130.93, 246.45)
# turning the avg. scores negative such that in the scaling they can be used as good indicator for dissatisfaction
avg_score   <- c(-8.45,-8.55,-8.32,-8.35,-8.42,-8.54)
avg_stay <- c(2.56,2.76,1.93,2.18,2.51,2.64)

city_info2  <- data_frame( vol, reviews_p_hotel, avg_score, avg_stay)   

rownames(city_info2)=c('Amsterdam', 'Barcelona', 'London','Milan', 'Paris', 'Vienna')

  xlab(' ') +

target_cities = c('London')
target_nations = c('United King*')

# reviews per city per nationality 
overview_uk = data %>%
  filter(str_detect(Reviewer_Nationality, target_nations)) %>%
  group_by(Hotel_location) %>%
  filter(Hotel_location %in% target_cities) %>%
  summarise(quantity = n(), avg_score = mean(Average_Score), avg_stay = mean(Stay_Duration)) %>%
  select(Hotel_location, quantity, avg_score, avg_stay) %>%
  arrange(desc(quantity))

# Get the Leisure proportion
leisure_uk = data %>%
  filter(str_detect(Reviewer_Nationality, target_nations)) %>%
  group_by(Hotel_location) %>%
  filter(Hotel_location %in% target_cities) %>%
  summarise(leisure = mean(leisure)) %>%
  select(Hotel_location, leisure)

# join the two tables
uk = inner_join(overview_uk,leisure_uk, by= 'Hotel_location')
